item.title: Nutrition
item.description: Over the last 3-4 years I've become more and more interested in nutrition and diet. My wakeup call was having blood analysis tests done and not having the best results. Up to that point in my life I never really cared that much about calories, salt, sugar or much of any type of food intake considerations. I would say my diet at the time was typical American and consisted of meats, cheese, chips, bread, and way too much sugar and salt.
